  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Evaluate pro-BNP levels, oxygen consumption, functional class, and quality of life in
      patients with chronic heart failure after participating in an exercise program and compare
      them baseline and 2 months, with another group who underwent an educational program.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Clinical controlled trial with a double blinded with a aleatory number sequence as the
      randomization method, patients will be assigned to one of two groups, intervention program
      (supervises exercise program) and control group (community based exercise)
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
